00:17:34,505 --> 00:17:37,965
How long are they going
to yap?! This is ticking me off!

243
00:17:38,005 --> 00:17:41,965
Son<i>-kun</i> looks like he was
bowled over by something!

244
00:17:42,005 --> 00:17:44,075
This is the biggest surprise of all!

245
00:17:44,115 --> 00:17:47,345
I thought for sure that Bulma
would take up with Yamucha.

246
00:17:47,385 --> 00:17:51,345
But instead, she goes with Vegeta there!

247
00:17:51,385 --> 00:17:55,415
Yamucha<i>-san</i> was, well...
something of a playboy,

248
00:17:55,455 --> 00:17:57,785
and she got fed up with him
and they split up, I understand.

249
00:17:59,955 --> 00:18:01,385
What's wrong?

250
00:18:01,425 --> 00:18:04,055
When she did, she saw how
alone my dad seemed, and somehow,

251
00:18:04,095 --> 00:18:06,925
before she realized what was happening...

252
00:18:06,965 --> 00:18:12,435
However, they never married.
That's just the way my mom is.

253
00:18:12,475 --> 00:18:14,405
Boy, I don't know.

254
00:18:14,445 --> 00:18:18,435
But when it comes to that
issue, it sounds just like her.

255
00:18:18,475 --> 00:18:23,005
My dad died before
I had any memories of him,

256
00:18:23,045 --> 00:18:26,445
so I was quite moved to
finally meet him a little while ago.

257
00:18:26,485 --> 00:18:28,945
He's looking over here at something.

258
00:18:28,985 --> 00:18:31,615
It looks like he's smiling a little.

259
00:18:33,495 --> 00:18:38,455
Now, please be sure to especially
keep this matter a secret, okay?

260
00:18:38,495 --> 00:18:41,095
If you say anything, and the feelings
between the two of them go bad,

261
00:18:41,135 --> 00:18:44,935
then my very existence will be erased!

262
00:18:44,975 --> 00:18:46,765
Yeah, I got it, I got it!

263
00:18:48,475 --> 00:18:51,935
Well then, I will excuse myself now.

264
00:18:51,975 --> 00:18:54,405
I want to return to the future and
reassure my mom as soon as I can.

265
00:18:54,445 --> 00:18:57,575
Sure. Tell her I said thanks for saving my life.

266
00:18:58,785 --> 00:19:00,945
It'll be nice if we can change the future, huh?

267
00:19:00,985 --> 00:19:05,955
Yes. Knowing your strength,
Goku<i>-san</i>, has raised my hopes.

268
00:19:05,995 --> 00:19:07,455
Will we meet again?

269
00:19:07,495 --> 00:19:08,925
I don't know.

270
00:19:08,965 --> 00:19:11,995
It takes a long time to
gather the energy necessary...

271
00:19:12,035 --> 00:19:14,665
...for the time machine to make a round trip.

272
00:19:14,705 --> 00:19:16,925
If I'm still alive after that time has passed,

273
00:19:16,965 --> 00:19:19,465
I will definitely come to help out!

274
00:19:19,505 --> 00:19:21,965
Three years from now.

275
00:19:22,005 --> 00:19:25,435
Be sure you survive.
You've got yourself a good goal.

276
00:19:25,475 --> 00:19:27,575
I'll be training as much as...

277
00:19:27,615 --> 00:19:30,105
...I can the next three
years for the same reason.

278
00:19:35,985 --> 00:19:38,115
Hey, he took off out of there!

279
00:19:42,495 --> 00:19:43,925
Now what do I do?

280
00:19:43,965 --> 00:19:46,955
How am I supposed to
explain this to everyone?

281
00:19:46,995 --> 00:19:49,465
Father!

282
00:19:49,505 --> 00:19:52,765
Goku! What did he say?

283
00:19:52,805 --> 00:19:55,795
Um, well, it wasn't all that much.

284
00:19:57,005 --> 00:20:01,445
Start talking. This is an
important matter for all of us, too.

285
00:20:01,485 --> 00:20:04,445
Piccolo, you overheard us?

286
00:20:04,485 --> 00:20:08,885
My sense of hearing is a bit
different from the rest of yours.

287
00:20:08,925 --> 00:20:11,355
What does he mean, an important matter?

288
00:20:11,395 --> 00:20:13,055
Tell us!

289
00:20:13,095 --> 00:20:14,385
Um, you see...

290
00:20:14,425 --> 00:20:18,395
If it's too hard for you to
tell them, I'll do it for you.

291
00:20:18,435 --> 00:20:19,895
Yeah, but–

292
00:20:19,935 --> 00:20:21,025
Don't worry.

293
00:20:21,065 --> 00:20:24,395
I won't say anything that
will threaten his existence.

294
00:20:24,435 --> 00:20:27,065
And we can't afford to let ourselves get killed...

295
00:20:27,105 --> 00:20:28,905
...because we didn't put in the due training.

296
00:20:28,945 --> 00:20:30,435
–Ki–
–Killed?!

297
00:20:31,445 --> 00:20:33,875
<i>Piccolo told everyone what was to happen,</i>

298
00:20:33,915 --> 00:20:39,115
<i>while skillfully leaving</i>
<i>Trunks' nature a mystery.</i>

299
00:20:41,955 --> 00:20:46,685
<i>As might be expected, no one</i>
<i>was able to conceal their shock.</i>

300
00:20:50,895 --> 00:20:53,725
Isn't this all a little hard to swallow?

301
00:20:53,765 --> 00:20:55,395
A time machine?

302
00:20:55,435 --> 00:20:59,395
Any of you who don't believe him,
that's fine. Enjoy yourselves.

303
00:20:59,435 --> 00:21:02,935
But I'm going to train,
because I don't want to die.

304
00:21:07,445 --> 00:21:09,075
What's that?!

305
00:21:15,955 --> 00:21:25,255
Dad, you were strong, proud,
stern, and lonesome, just as Mom said.

306
00:21:25,295 --> 00:21:27,425
Please don't die.

307
00:21:27,465 --> 00:21:30,635
Young Mom, you hang in there too.

308
00:21:45,455 --> 00:21:46,785
He vanished!

309
00:21:55,465 --> 00:21:57,325
I'm going to train.

310
00:21:57,365 --> 00:21:58,825
Me too.

311
00:21:58,865 --> 00:22:01,425
I'm in too.

312
00:22:01,465 --> 00:22:07,135
<i>Dammit, three years from</i>
<i>now I am going to survive!</i>

313
00:22:11,945 --> 00:22:17,415
<i>Having delivered the hard truth,</i>
<i>the mysterious young man departed.</i>

314
00:22:17,455 --> 00:22:23,785
<i>Will such a terrible pair</i>
<i>really appear in three years?</i>

315
00:22:44,645 --> 00:22:48,645
<i>Here it comes a-fighting,</i>
<i>an apple-colored monster,</i>

316
00:22:48,685 --> 00:22:54,485
<i>Here it comes a-flying,</i>
<i>a nut-scented alien,</i>

317
00:22:54,525 --> 00:22:56,855
<i>They meet and the heart beats faster.</i>

318
00:23:00,325 --> 00:23:05,355
<i>Sparkle, sparkle, the galaxy's a popcorn shower.</i>

319
00:23:07,665 --> 00:23:11,865
<i>Yesterday goes bye, bye, bye, (Gohan),</i>

320
00:23:11,905 --> 00:23:15,965
<i>Mystery, (far as the eye can see),</i>

321
00:23:16,005 --> 00:23:19,475
<i>Gather up your energy, (substitutes are okay),</i>

322
00:23:19,515 --> 00:23:22,105
<i>Come over here, lai, lai, lai.</i>

323
00:23:23,845 --> 00:23:29,615
<i>Ooh, miracle ZENKAI power!</i>

324
00:23:31,855 --> 00:23:33,715
<i>A hungry, naughty Kinto Un,</i>

325
00:23:33,755 --> 00:23:35,525
<i>A mountain full of horizons.</i>

326
00:23:35,565 --> 00:23:39,555
<i>They meet each other, they come apart,</i>
<i>they meet each other, they come apart, Oh, no!</i>

327
00:23:39,595 --> 00:23:45,235
<i>Aah, enough! Even Kami-sama has it rough.</i>

328
00:23:45,275 --> 00:23:47,405
<i>So sorry.</i>

329
00:23:47,445 --> 00:23:52,535
<i>Ooh, full-bellied ZENKAI power!</i>

330
00:23:55,285 --> 00:24:00,545
<i>Come on out, full-on ZENKAI power!</i>

331
00:24:12,065 --> 00:24:13,795
<i>Heya! I'm Goku!</i>

332
00:24:13,835 --> 00:24:16,365
<i>All right, everyone,</i>
<i>let's meet up again in three years.</i>

333
00:24:16,405 --> 00:24:18,135
<i>Those of you who are</i>
<i>sure of yourselves, anyhow.</i>

334
00:24:18,175 --> 00:24:20,965
<i>Artificial Humans are apparently</i>
<i>even worse than anything before.</i>

335
00:24:21,005 --> 00:24:25,905
<i>Before that, Kakarrot, tell us</i>
<i>how you survived on Planet Namek!</i>

336
00:24:25,945 --> 00:24:27,905
<i>Next time on Dragon Ball Z,</i>

